Yes.

In addition, I&#39;d recommend no=
t to make use of type attributes because they lead to unintended coupling b=
etween representations (or the code that produces these representations) an=
d the set of used media types. Any time you remove or add support for a cer=
tain media type, you need to check and update all the code that produces co=
rresponding &#39;type&#39; attributes. That&#39;s likely to be a maintenance nightmare.=




